South African Inflation Expectations Rose in Third Quarter

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-09-22T13:04:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/south-african-inflation-expectations-rose-in-third-quarter.html
South African inflation
expectations rose in the third quarter compared with the
previous three months, the Bureau for  Economic Research  said.  Analysts, labor unions and business people expect the
inflation rate to average 5.9 percent in 2012, according to a
third-quarter survey, compared with 5.8 percent estimated in a
second-quarter survey, the bureau said in an e-mailed statement
today. Inflation is forecast to reach 5.5 percent in 2011 from
5.3 percent in the previous survey and accelerate to 5.9 percent
in 2013, the survey said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  